      <title>Codingfish Roadmap 2014</title>
      <author>Achim Fischer</author>
      <pubDate>Mon, 30 Dec 2013 12:54:02 +0100</pubDate>
      <link>https://www.codingfish.com/blog/123-codingfish-roadmap-2014</link>
      <guid>123</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;
                &lt;p&gt;&lt;img src='https://www.codingfish.com/system/blog_articles/images/000/000/123/large/roadmap-2014.jpg?1402429238' alt='Codingfish Roadmap 2014' title='Codingfish Roadmap 2014' align='' /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
              On February 1st, 2014 I will join the Android team at &lt;a href="http://www.medion.com" title="Medion" target="_blank"&gt;Medion&lt;/a&gt; in Essen, Germany as a "Senior&amp;nbsp;Software&amp;nbsp;Engineer". In this new regular job I will help to create great Android devices with our team in Essen and our partners in China.
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;

This fulltime job will of course affect all my other projects. In short I would say:
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;

&lt;b&gt;Much less (almost zero) Joomla!, a bit more Ruby on Rails and much more Android.&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;


&lt;!-- READMORE --&gt;


&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
Here is more info about my projects: 
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;Joomla! / My Joomla! extensions&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
In 2013 I already discontinued the extension "Marketplace" and the module "Vernissage".
Due to the lack of time in 2014 I will pause the development for my forum extension "Discussions". I do not say it's dead (yet) but don't expect any further development in the foreseeable future. 
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;



&lt;h3&gt;Chimoora&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
In my sparetime I'm working on a Content Management System (CMS) which will replace my Joomla! installation on &lt;a href="http://www.codingfish.com" title="codingfish.com" target="_blank"&gt;codingfish.com&lt;/a&gt; as soon as all needed features are implemented. Chimoora is developed using Ruby on Rails 4 and Bootstrap 3.
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;


&lt;h3&gt;Websites&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.codingfish.com" title="codingfish.com" target="_blank"&gt;codingfish.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
My website will be relaunched as soon as Chimoora is ready for production use. The currently running Joomla! 2.5 will then be replaced.
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.italobikes.com" title="italobikes.com" target="_blank"&gt;italobikes.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
My online community about italian motorcycles is still running Joomla! 1.5 and will relaunch on Chimoora after it has been tested extensively on &lt;a href="http://www.codingfish.com" title="codingfish.com" target="_blank"&gt;codingfish.com&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a href="http://fuldany.de" title="fuldany.de" target="_blank"&gt;fuldany.de&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
The Ruby on Rails based social network for my hometown &lt;a href="http://www.fulda.de" title="Fulda" target="_blank"&gt;Fulda&lt;/a&gt; has been launched in 2013. New features will be added in 2014.
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;





&lt;h3&gt;Apps for Mobile Devices&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.codingfish.codingfish" title="Codingfish for Android" target="_blank"&gt;Codingfish for Android&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; will be replaced with a new version when the new CMS goes online.
&lt;br&gt;
Work on my Joomla! API extension and the &lt;strong&gt;Chimoora&lt;/strong&gt; app (Android and iOS) for Joomla! will be stopped.
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.codingfish.fuldany" title="Fuldany for Android" target="_blank"&gt;Fuldany for Android&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; and 

&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://itunes.apple.com/app/fuldany/id680274790?mt=8" title="Fuldany for iOS" target="_blank"&gt;Fuldany for iOS&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; have high priority because they are needed to support my local social network (see above).
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;



&lt;h3&gt;Events&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
Nothing planned yet and I'm not sure if I will be able to attend many events in 2014. I will have to travel in my new job so it's difficult to plan anything now. Anyway, Android related events will have high priority.
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;



&lt;h3&gt;Photography&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
I will spend a bit more time increasing my photography skills. Here are some of my photos (more to come): &lt;a href="http://500px.com/codingfish" title="Codingfish on 500px" target="_blank"&gt;Codingfish on 500px&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;




&lt;br&gt;
Thank you. May you all have a great year 2014 :-)
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;

Achim
&lt;/p&gt;</description>
